Ax^2+Bxy+Cy^2
x=\cos t,y=\sin t
Ax^2+Bxy+Cy^2=A\cos^2t+B\sin t\cos t+C\sin^2t
A\cos^2t+B\sin t\cos t+C\sin^2t=P
\cos^2t, A+B\tan t+C\tan^2t=P\sec^2t
A+B\tan t+C\tan^2t=P(1+\tan^2t)
\tan t
\implies (C-P)\tan^2t+B\tan t+A-P=0
t
\tan t,
B^2-4(A-P)(C-P)\ge 0
B^2-4(A-P)(C-P)
=B^2-4AC-\{4P^2-4P(A+C)\}
=B^2-4AC+(A+C)^2-\{4P^2-4P(A+C)+(A+C)^2\}
=B^2+(A-C)^2-\{2P-(A+C)\}^2
\implies B^2+(A-C)^2-\{2P-(A+C)\}^2\ge0
\implies \{2P-(A+C)\}^2\le B^2+(A-C)^2
y^2\le a^2\implies -a\le y\le a
\implies -\sqrt{B^2+(A-C)^2}\le 2P-(A+C)\le \sqrt{B^2+(A-C)^2} 
\implies \frac{A+C-\sqrt{B^2+(A-C)^2}}2\le P\le \frac{A+C+\sqrt{B^2+(A-C)^2}}2
A=3,B=5,C=-4
